6.00	Franklin_bells	Franklin bells	Franklin bells are an early demonstration of electric charge designed to work with a Leyden jar. They were invented by Benjamin Franklin in the 18th century during his experimentation with electricity. Franklin bells are only a qualitative indicator of electric charge and were used for simple demonstrations rather than research.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/20/Franklinbells.jpg/220px-Franklinbells.jpg
